{% comment %}
  PRIVACY POLICY PAGE TEMPLATE
  Shopify Liquid template for privacy policy
  Displays company privacy policy information
{% endcomment %}

<!-- Policy Container -->
<section class="policy-page" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}" data-section-type="policy">
  <div class="policy-page__inner">
    <div class="policy-header">
      <h1 class="policy-header__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="policy-header__date">Last updated: November 19, 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="policy-content">
      <p>
        Quinton Stocton Photography operates this store and website, including all related information, content, features, tools, products and services, in order to provide you, the customer, with a curated shopping experience (the "Services"). Quinton Stocton Photography is powered by Shopify, which enables us to provide the Services to you. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information when you visit, use, or make a purchase or other transaction using the Services or otherwise communicate with us.
      </p>

      <h2>Personal Information We Collect</h2>

      <p>When we use the term "personal information," we are referring to information that identifies or can reasonably be linked to you or another person. We may collect or process the following categories of personal information, depending on how you interact with the Services:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact details</strong> including your name, address, phone number, and email address.</li>
        <li><strong>Financial information</strong> including payment card information and transaction details.</li>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> including your username, password, and preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>Transaction information</strong> including items you view, purchase, or add to your cart.</li>
        <li><strong>Device information</strong> including your device, browser, IP address, and other unique identifiers.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage information</strong> including information about how you interact with the Services.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>

      <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Provide and Improve Services:</strong> To perform our contract with you, process payments, fulfill orders, and provide customer support.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> To send marketing communications, promotional offers, and personalized advertising.</li>
        <li><strong>Security and Fraud Prevention:</strong> To detect and prevent fraudulent activity and protect your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> To comply with applicable law and respond to legal requests.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Protection & Security</h2>

      <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on where you reside, you may have certain legal rights regarding your personal information, including the right to access, correct, delete, or port your data. To exercise these rights, please contact us at customersupport@quintonstoctonphotography.com.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>

      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:<br>
        Email: customersupport@quintonstoctonphotography.com<br>
        Phone: +1 (270) 283-7950
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    margin-top: 80px;
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    background: #000;
  }

  .policy-page__inner {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .policy-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-base-primary);
  }

  .policy-header__title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .policy-header__date {
    color: var(--color-base-primary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .policy-content {
    color: #E5E0E0;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policy-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-base-border);
  }

  .policy-content ul {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .policy-content li {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-content strong {
    color: var(--color-base-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-page {
      margin-top: 60px;
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .policy-header__title {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    .policy-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .policy-content {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  }
</style>
